---
title: Git Intel — Data Flow (per run_once cycle)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant CFG  as 📄 config.json
    participant MAIN as 🚀 main.py
    participant GP   as 🔍 git_parser.py
    participant GIT  as 🗂️ Git Repo
    participant LC   as 🤖 llm_client.py
    participant OAI  as ☁️ OpenAI API
    participant LW   as 💾 log_writer.py
    participant FS   as 🗄️ store/ (disk)
    participant DB   as 🌐 Dashboard

    Note over MAIN,CFG: Startup
    MAIN ->> CFG: load config.json
    CFG -->> MAIN: {api_key, model, repos, schedule, …}

    rect rgb(219, 234, 254)
        Note over MAIN,FS: run_once() — repeated each scheduled interval
        loop For each configured repository

            Note over MAIN,GP: Step 1 — Snapshot working tree
            MAIN ->> GP: get_file_tree(repo_path)
            GP ->> GIT: os.walk / Path.iterdir()
            GIT -->> GP: directory + file entries
            GP -->> MAIN: nested tree dict
            MAIN ->> LW: write_file_tree(name, tree)
            LW ->> FS: store/&lt;repo&gt;-tree.json ✏️

            Note over MAIN,GIT: Step 2 — Detect new commits
            MAIN ->> LW: get_last_sha(name)
            LW ->> FS: read store/&lt;repo&gt;.json
            FS -->> LW: existing entries (or empty)
            LW -->> MAIN: last_seen_sha (or None)
            MAIN ->> GP: get_commits(path, last_sha, lookback)
            GP ->> GIT: repo.iter_commits(branch)
            GIT -->> GP: commit objects
            GP -->> MAIN: list of commit dicts<br/>{sha, author, timestamp,<br/> message, stats, changed_files}

            alt New commits found
                Note over MAIN,OAI: Step 3a — Summarise with LLM
                MAIN ->> LC: summarise(api_key, model, commits)
                LC ->> LC: build_prompt(commits)
                LC ->> OAI: chat.completions.create(model, messages)
                OAI -->> LC: ChatCompletion<br/>{choices[0].message.content,<br/> usage.prompt_tokens,<br/> usage.completion_tokens,<br/> usage.total_tokens}
                LC ->> LC: _extract_usage(response)
                LC -->> MAIN: (summary_str, token_usage_dict)

                Note over MAIN,FS: Step 3b — Persist results
                MAIN ->> LW: make_entry(summary, commits, token_usage)
                LW -->> MAIN: entry dict<br/>{timestamp, commit_range,<br/> summary, files_changed,<br/> insertions, deletions,<br/> changed_files, token_usage}
                MAIN ->> LW: append_entry(name, entry)
                LW ->> FS: store/&lt;repo&gt;.json ✏️

                MAIN ->> LW: append_token_log(name, model, token_usage)
                LW ->> FS: store/token_usage.json ✏️

            else No new commits
                MAIN ->> MAIN: print "[repo] No new commits"
            end
        end

        Note over MAIN,FS: Step 4 — Update dashboard manifest
        MAIN ->> LW: write_index(repo_names)
        LW ->> FS: store/index.json ✏️
    end

    Note over DB,FS: Dashboard reads (on-demand, via browser)
    DB ->> FS: GET /store/index.json
    FS -->> DB: ["repo-a", "repo-b"]
    DB ->> FS: GET /store/&lt;repo&gt;.json
    FS -->> DB: [{id, timestamp, summary,<br/> token_usage, …}, …]
    DB ->> FS: GET /store/&lt;repo&gt;-tree.json
    FS -->> DB: {name, type, children:[…]}
    Note over DB: Renders timeline + file tree in browser
